{
    "directions": [
        "Remove rinds and seeds from melons and cut fruit into 1/4-inch dice. Cut bell pepper into 1/4-inch dice. Finely chop onion and cilantro and, wearing rubber gloves, finely chop jalape\u00f1o with seeds. In a bowl toss together all ingredients and season with salt. Salsa may be made 4 hours ahead and chilled, covered."
    ],
    "ingredients": [
        "a 1-pound piece watermelon",
        "a 1-pound piece cantaloupe",
        "1/2 red bell pepper",
        "1/2 small sweet onion such as Vidalia",
        "1/3 cup packed fresh cilantro sprigs",
        "1/2 fresh jalape\u00f1o chile",
        "2 tablespoons chopped fresh mint leaves",
        "1 tablespoon fresh lime juice"
